    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050">
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a core relation that holds between a part and its whole</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Everything is part of itself. Any part of any part of a thing is itself part of that thing. Two distinct things cannot be part of each other.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Occurrents are not subject to change and so parthood between occurrents holds for all the times that the part exists. Many continuants are subject to change, so parthood between continuants will only hold at certain times, but this is difficult to specify in OWL. See http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/temporal-semantics/</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Parthood requires the part and the whole to have compatible classes: only an occurrent can be part of an occurrent; only a process can be part of a process; only a continuant can be part of a continuant; only an independent continuant can be part of an independent continuant; only an immaterial entity can be part of an immaterial entity; only a specifically dependent continuant can be part of a specifically dependent continuant; only a generically dependent continuant can be part of a generically dependent continuant. (This list is not exhaustive.)

A continuant cannot be part of an occurrent: use &apos;participates in&apos;. An occurrent cannot be part of a continuant: use &apos;has participant&apos;. A material entity cannot be part of an immaterial entity: use &apos;has location&apos;. A specifically dependent continuant cannot be part of an independent continuant: use &apos;inheres in&apos;. An independent continuant cannot be part of a specifically dependent continuant: use &apos;bearer of&apos;.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">part of</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a core relation that holds between a whole and its part</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Everything has itself as a part. Any part of any part of a thing is itself part of that thing. Two distinct things cannot have each other as a part.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Occurrents are not subject to change and so parthood between occurrents holds for all the times that the part exists. Many continuants are subject to change, so parthood between continuants will only hold at certain times, but this is difficult to specify in OWL. See http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/temporal-semantics/</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Parthood requires the part and the whole to have compatible classes: only an occurrent have an occurrent as part; only a process can have a process as part; only a continuant can have a continuant as part; only an independent continuant can have an independent continuant as part; only a specifically dependent continuant can have a specifically dependent continuant as part; only a generically dependent continuant can have a generically dependent continuant as part. (This list is not exhaustive.)

A continuant cannot have an occurrent as part: use &apos;participates in&apos;. An occurrent cannot have a continuant as part: use &apos;has participant&apos;. An immaterial entity cannot have a material entity as part: use &apos;location of&apos;. An independent continuant cannot have a specifically dependent continuant as part: use &apos;bearer of&apos;. A specifically dependent continuant cannot have an independent continuant as part: use &apos;inheres in&apos;.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has part</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000055">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Paraphrase of elucidation: a relation between a process and a realizable entity, where there is some material entity that is bearer of the realizable entity and participates in the process, and the realizable entity comes to be realized in the course of the process</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">realizes</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">(Elucidation) realizes is a relation between a process b and realizable entity c such that c inheres in some d &amp; for all t, if b has participant d then c exists &amp; the type instantiated by b is correlated with the type instantiated by c</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">A balding process realizes a disposition to go bald; a studying process realizes a student role; a process of pumping blood realizes the pumping function of a heart</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000062 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000062">
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000063"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff ω(y) &lt;= α(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">preceded by</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">b preceded by c =Def b precedes c</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">The temporal region occupied by the second half of the match is preceded by the temporal region occupied by the first half of the match</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000063 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000063">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">x precedes y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x precedes y iff ω(x) &lt;= α(y), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">precedes</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">(Elucidation) precedes is a relation between occurrents o, o&apos; such that if t is the temporal extent of o &amp; t&apos; is the temporal extent of o&apos; then either the last instant of o is before the first instant of o&apos; or the last instant of o is the first instant of o&apos; &amp; neither o nor o&apos; are temporal instants</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">The temporal region occupied by Mary&apos;s birth precedes the temporal region occupied by Mary&apos;s death.</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000108 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000108">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">exists at</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">(Elucidation) exists at is a relation between a particular and some temporal region at which the particular exists</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">First World War exists at 1914-1916; Mexico exists at January 1, 2000</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has occurrent part</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">b has occurrent part c =Def c occurrent part of b</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">Mary&apos;s life has occurrent part Mary&apos;s 5th birthday</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000138 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000138">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">proper occurrent part of</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">b proper occurrent part of c =Def b occurrent part of c &amp; b and c are not identical</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">As for occurrent part of.</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000222 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000222">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has first instant</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">t has first instant t&apos; =Def t&apos; first instant of t</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">The first hour of a year has first instant midnight on December 31</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000224 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000224">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has last instant</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">t has last instant t&apos; =Def t&apos; last instant of t</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">The last hour of a year has last instant midnight December 31</skos:example>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has measurement unit label</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">7/6/2009 Alan Ruttenberg. Following discussion with Jonathan Rees, and introduction of &quot;mentions&quot; relation. Weaken the is_about relationship to be primitive. 

We will try to build it back up by elaborating the various subproperties that are more precisely defined.

Some currently missing phenomena that should be considered &quot;about&quot; are predications - &quot;The only person who knows the answer is sitting beside me&quot; , Allegory, Satire, and other literary forms that can be topical without explicitly mentioning the topic.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is about</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000219 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000219">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136"/>
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000235"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A primitive, instance-level, relation obtaining between an information content entity and some portion of reality. Denotation is what happens when someone creates an information content entity E in order to specifically refer to something. The only relation between E and the thing is that E can be used to &apos;pick out&apos; the thing. This relation connects those two together. Freedictionary.com sense 3: To signify directly; refer to specifically</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">2009-11-10 Alan Ruttenberg. Old definition said the following to emphasize the generic nature of this relation. We no longer have &apos;specifically denotes&apos;, which would have been primitive, so make this relation primitive.
g denotes r =def 
r is a portion of reality
there is some c that is a concretization of g 
every c that is a concretization of g specifically denotes r</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">denotes</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000235 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000235">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">inverse of the relation &apos;denotes&apos;</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">denoted by</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000293">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The inverse property of is specified input of</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>8/17/09: specified inputs of one process are not necessarily specified inputs of a larger process that it is part of. This is in contrast to how &apos;has participant&apos; works.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has specified input</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057"/>
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000312"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>The inverse property of is specified output of</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has specified output</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000312 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000312">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A relation between a completely executed planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">is specified output of</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001938 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001938">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A relation between an information content entity and a value specification that specifies its value.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label>has value specification</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#InverseFunctionalProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Inverse of characteristic_of</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">A bearer can have many dependents, and its dependents can exist for different periods of time, but none of its dependents can exist when the bearer does not exist.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has characteristic</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057">
        <owl:propertyChainAxiom rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000057"/>
        </owl:propertyChainAxiom>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">Has_participant is a primitive instance-level relation between a process, a continuant, and a time at which the continuant participates in some way in the process. The relation obtains, for example, when this particular process of oxygen exchange across this particular alveolar membrane has_participant this particular sample of hemoglobin at this particular time.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has participant</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A relationship between a specifically dependent continuant and a generically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. Multiple specifically dependent continuants can concretize the same generically dependent continuant.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A relationship between a specifically dependent continuant or process and a generically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant or process also depends on that same independent continuant. Multiple specifically dependent continuants or processes can concretize the same generically dependent continuant.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">concretizes</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080">
        <owl:inverseOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between a quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">A quality inheres in its bearer at all times for which the quality exists.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quality of</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a function, in which the function specifically depends on the bearer for its existence</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">A bearer can have many functions, and its functions can exist for different periods of time, but none of its functions can exist when the bearer does not exist. A function need not be realized at all the times that the function exists.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has function</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a quality, in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">A bearer can have many qualities, and its qualities can exist for different periods of time, but none of its qualities can exist when the bearer does not exist.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has quality</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000087 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000087">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000053"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a role, in which the role specifically depends on the bearer for its existence</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">A bearer can have many roles, and its roles can exist for different periods of time, but none of its roles can exist when the bearer does not exist. A role need not be realized at all the times that the role exists.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">has role</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0001000 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0001000">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">a relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">This is a very general relation. More specific relations are preferred when applicable, such as &apos;directly develops from&apos;.</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">derives from</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002224 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002224">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>x starts with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: α(y) = α(x) ∧ ω(y) &lt; ω(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">starts with</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002230 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002230">
        <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>x ends with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: α(y) &gt; α(x) ∧ ω(y) = ω(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ends with</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">A relation between an assay and a characteristic, in which the assay generates a data item which is a measure of a characteristic.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">assay measures characteristic</rdfs:label>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- http://www.w3.org/ns/csvw#column -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/ns/csvw#column"/>
    


    <!-- http://www.w3.org/ns/csvw#tableSchema -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/ns/csvw#tableSchema"/>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077 -->

    <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000077">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">specified by value</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A relation between an entity and a value specification which is about this entity.</skos:definition>
    </owl:ObjectProperty>
    


    <!-- 
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
    //
    // Classes
    //
    ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
     -->

    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3 (generic upper-level HT-process taxonomy)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.167 (Härtung)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.207 (thermochemische Behandlung)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.8 (Glühen)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">intermediate class/grouping term, not to be instatialized</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Grundsätzlicher Wärmebehandlungsvorgang</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat treatment operation</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Essential processes that make up heat treatments and can be used like building blocks.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000001 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000001">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.168</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenching function</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A quenching function is a (realizable) function that, when realized, enables a system to lower the temparature of a material fast enough, that it hinders diffusion processes and thus produces metastable material states.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Eine Abschreckfunktion ist eine (realisierbare) Funktion, die es einem System ermöglicht die Temperatur eines Material schnell genug abzusenken, sodass Diffusionsprozesse behindert und dadurch metastabile Materialzustände erzeugt werden.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="en">The function of a oil bath to quench steel after austenitisation so the material transforms into martensite.</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000002 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000002">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hardening recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A hardeing recipe describing the steps and conditions for carrying out a hardening process.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000003 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000003">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000005"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.2</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature change rate specification</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A setpoint which - as part of plan specifications (e.g. recipes) - specifies the rate at which temparature is to be changed.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000004 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000004">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000003"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000006"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heating recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe describing the steps and parameters for carrying out a heating process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept mit dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Aufheizprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000005 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000005">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.2 (incl. kritische Abkühlgeschwindigkeit K_k)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature change rate</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A process attribute defining the change of temperature per time unit within a process.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000006 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000006">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000010"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5 (generic process-target temperature)</terms:source>
        <oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym xml:lang="en">target temperature specification</oboInOwl:hasRelatedSynonym>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">target temperature</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A setpoint defining the temperature that is to be reached/held within a process that involves a defined temperature.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote>needs work</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000008 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000008">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000009"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (Verweildauer / Erwärm-/Anwärm-/Durchwärm-/Haltedauer)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11 Fn d, f</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">duration specification</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>Device specification as part of a plan specification which specifies the duration of a given process.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000009 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000009">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (Verweildauer/Erwärm-/Anwärm-/Durchwärm-/Haltedauer)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11 (Anlassdauer / Aust.-dauer)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">duration</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">a temporal interval that describes the temporal extent of a process which is demarcated by the distance of two temporal instants</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000010 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000010">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018 (generic, °C usage throughout)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>working variable, used for testing only</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature unit</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000011 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000011">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.14</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-5:2021, Tab.7 col.3</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>needs more work; austenitic phase can be reached from at least two temperatures for any given material (from liquid or from ferrite)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">austenitizing point</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A realizable entity of a material which marks the phase change to austenite (γ-iron).</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000012 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000012">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.185</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">holding function</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment function that, enables a system or device to hold the thermal energy of a material, typically to facilitate diffusion and phase transformation processes within the material.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example>function of a furnace to hold its temperature at a specified temperature</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000013 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000013">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000002"/>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000004"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000014"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000015"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000016"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, Tab.8</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>add target temperature in axioms, combine it with austenitisation temperature</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hardening heat treatment recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe describing the steps and conditions for carrying out a hardening heat treatment process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept mit dem Schritte und Parameter für die Durchführung eines Härtungsprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000014 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000014">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000006"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000008"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.185</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">holding recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe outlining the steps and parameters for carrying out a holding process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept, in dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Halteprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000015 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000015">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000006"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000008"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (Durchwärmdauer)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.185</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">soaking recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe outlining the steps and parameters for carrying out a soaking process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept, in dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Durchwärmprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000016 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000016">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000017"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.168</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenching recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe describing the steps and conditions for carrying out a quenching process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept mit dem Schritte und Parameter für die Durchführung eines Abschreckprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000017 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000017">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.45</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept mit dem Schritte und Parameter für die Durchführung eines Abkühlungsprozesses beschrieben werden.</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooling recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe describing the steps and parameters for carrying out a cooling process.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000018 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000018">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nitriding recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe outlining the steps and parameters for carrying out a nitriding process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept, in dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Nitrierprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000019 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000019">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000020"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-5:2000, §1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-5:2000, §4</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.200</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Oberflächenhärtung</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">surface hardening</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Oberflächenhärtung</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Randschichthärtung</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Auf die Randschicht beschränkte Härtung (3.167).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Hardening (3.167) restricted to the surface layer.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition>Hardening process where only the surface of a part and not its entire volume is hardened.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit fix (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.200 lemma is &apos;Randschichthärten&apos;; DIN 17022-5 uses &apos;Randschichthärten&apos; exclusively in its title. The hto-edit.owl DE label &apos;Oberflächenhärtung&apos; is a DIN-10052 / legacy synonym (already retained in hto-edit.owl as skos:altLabel — preserved here). The DIN-canonical &apos;Randschichthärten&apos; is hoisted to skos:prefLabel.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000020 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000020">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.209</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Durchhärten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">through hardening</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>Hardening (3.167), in which the formation of martensite (3.137) extends right to the core of a workpiece.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Härtung (3.167), bei der die Bildung von Martensit (3.137) bis zum Kern eines Werkstückes erreicht wird.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000021 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000021">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000013"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000023"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.3</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.169</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">QT recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe outlining the steps and parameters for carrying out a quenching and tempering process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept, in dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Vergütungsprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000022 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000022">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="genid33"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000038"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000117"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom>
                            <owl:Class>
                                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                                    <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
                                    <owl:Restriction>
                                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000063"/>
                                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000038"/>
                                    </owl:Restriction>
                                </owl:intersectionOf>
                            </owl:Class>
                        </owl:someValuesFrom>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.3</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.169</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.1 Zeile 5 (+QT)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Vergüten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenching and tempering</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Abschrecken und Anlassen</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">QT</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Hardening (3.167) of a workpiece, followed by tempering, in order to produce a condition characterised by a good combination of hardness and toughness.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Härtung (3.167) eines Werkstückes mit anschließendem Anlassen, um einen Zustand zu erzeugen, der durch eine gute Kombination von Härte und Zähigkeit gekennzeichnet ist.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Class rdf:nodeID="genid33">
        <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000020"/>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000038"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </owl:intersectionOf>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000022"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget rdf:nodeID="genid33"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000116>this axiom should also include the order of the process (hardening precedes tempering)</obo:IAO_0000116>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000023 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000023">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.4</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-5:2000, §6.5</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.203</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, Tab.8</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>add target temperature in axioms</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tempering recipe</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment recipe outlining the steps and parameters for carrying out a tempering process.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungsrezept, in dem die Schritte und Parameter zur Durchführung eines Anlassprozesses beschrieben werden.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000024 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000024">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000041"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">plasma nitriding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A nitriding process in which nitrogen is supplied to the surface via the acceleration of ionised nitrogen.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Nitriding (3.143) at a pressure that is usually below atmospheric pressure, using a plasma carrier to ionise the nitrogen.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Nitrieren (3.143) bei einem Druck, der üblicherweise unter dem Atmosphärendruck liegt und mit einem Plasmaträger, um den Stickstoff zu ionisieren</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000025 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000025">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.36</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Aufkohlen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">carburizing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Karburieren</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition>A surface hardening process in which carbon is supplied to a material&apos;s surface with the goal to increase the carbon content in the surface of a sample or part.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Thermochemical treatment (3.207) to enrich the surface of an austenitised workpiece with carbon, which is then present in solid solution in austenite (3.12).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Thermochemische Behandlung (3.207) zum Anreichern der Oberfläche eines austenitisierten Werkstückes mit Kohlenstoff, der dann im Austenit (3.12) in fester Lösung vorliegt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit fix (2026-06-09): hto-edit.owl&apos;s existing rdfs:comment/skos:definition treats Aufkohlen as a &apos;surface hardening process&apos;; DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.36 defines it as &apos;thermochemische Behandlung zum Anreichern der Oberfläche eines austenitisierten Werkstückes mit Kohlenstoff&apos;. Hardening only follows IF quenching is subsequently applied (cf. §3.37 Einsatzhärten = Aufkohlen + Härten). Original rdfs:label preserved; the §3.36 verbatim definition is added via skos:definition as the canonical anchor.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000026 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000026">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000041"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.143 (inline)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Gasnitrieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas nitriding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A nitriding process where nitrogen is supplied to the surface in gaseous form.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000027 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000027">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (Ofendruck &lt; 10 mbar, Plasmanitrieren)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">target pressure</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A setpoint describing the pressure that is to be reached/held within a process that involves a defined pressure.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote>needs work</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000028 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000028">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000085"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000029"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (atmosphere supply equipment, inline)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mass flow controller</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Device that has the function to control the flow of fluid media to a defined mass flow. It consists of a mass flow meter and a proportional valve.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000029 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000029">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (atmosphere flow measurement)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow measuring function</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A measuring function performed to determine the flow of fluids.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000030 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000030">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000005"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 5</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1.1 (Aufheizgeschwindigkeit)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heating rate</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A temperature change rate that is of positive value.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000031 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000031">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000005"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5.2.2 (Abkühlgeschwindigkeit)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.52 (kritische Abkühlgeschwindigkeit)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooling rate</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A temperature change rate that is of negative value.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032">
        <terms:creator>thonagel</terms:creator>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §5 (Sollwert / Solltemperatur, procedural usage)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>Internally (within the devices&apos; logic) a process is run to reach and maintain the given setpoint.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Sollwert</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">setpoint</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A Set Point is a specification datum that assigns a desired quantitative value to a controlled process parameter, serving as the normative reference for process execution and control.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Ein Sollwert ist ein Spezifikationswert, der einem geregelten Prozessparameter einen gewünschten quantitativen Wert zuweist und als normgebende Referenz für die Prozessausführung und -steuerung dient.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 does not enumerate &apos;Sollwert&apos; as a §3 lemma; PMDco owns the generic &apos;setpoint&apos; concept upstream. The DIN procedural anchor is DIN 17022-1 §5 (Sollwert / Solltemperatur operational usage). Provenance is therefore procedural rather than terminological.</skos:editorialNote>
        <skos:example>The flow rate for a mass flow controller.
The target temperature in the furnace chamber for a given process step.
The rotational speed of a fan.</skos:example>
        <co:PMD_0000064>tdb</co:PMD_0000064>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000033 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000033">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000034"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:creator>thonagel</terms:creator>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">device operation state</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A Device Operation State is a state that inheres in a device and specifies whether a device function is currently active or inactive, typically represented in a control or output protocol as an on/off (or analogous binary) indicator.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Switches are device specifications that triggers a certain function within a device that can only assume two states (on/off).</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000034 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000034">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">device operation state value</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A categorical value specification defining the on/off state of some device.</skos:definition>
        <co:PMD_0000060 rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</co:PMD_0000060>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000037 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000037">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000041"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §8</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.143 (inline)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Salzbadnitrieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">salt bath nitriding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A nitriding process in which nitrogen is supplied to the surface by molten salt.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000038 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000038">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000062"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.203</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Anlassen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tempering</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) of a steel product, generally carried out following hardening (3.167) or another heat treatment to achieve the required levels of properties, consisting of heating (3.109) to specific temperatures (&lt; A1) and holding at these temperatures once or several times, followed by appropriate cooling (3.45)</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108) eines Eisenerzeugnisses, die im Allgemeinen nach einem Härten (3.167) oder einer anderen Wärmebehandlung zum Erreichen geforderter Stufen für Eigenschaften durchgeführt wird, bestehend aus Erwärmen (3.109) auf bestimmte Temperaturen (&lt; A1) und einmaliges oder mehrmaliges Halten und anschließendem zweckentsprechendem Abkühlen (3.45)</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.8</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Glühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108), consisting of heating (3.109) and soaking (3.185) at a suitable temperature followed by cooling (3.45), such that an equilibrium-near microstructure is reached at room temperature.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment process to form a specific microstructure or reduce residual stresses.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108), bestehend aus Erwärmen (3.109) und Halten (3.185) auf einer geeigneten Temperatur sowie Abkühlen (3.45), so dass sich bei Raumtemperatur ein dem Gleichgewicht angenäherter Gefügezustand einstellt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung um eine bestimmte Gefügeausbildung zu erzielen oder Spannungen zu reduzieren.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit fix (2026-06-09): hto-edit.owl HTO_0000039 currently has only an @en label &apos;annealing&apos; and no DE label. DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.8 lemma is &apos;Glühen&apos;. The DE label is added via skos:prefLabel. NB: 4885 §3.8 Anm.1 organises Glühen as a parent of named children (Blankglühen, Normalglühen, Weichglühen, zwischenkritisches Glühen, isothermes Umwandeln, etc.); subclasses HTO_0000093..HTO_0000102 below populate this Glühen-family per DIN 683-7 §6.2.1 granularity contract.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000013"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §3.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.167</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Härtung durch Wärmebehandlung</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hardening heat treatment</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment process to increase the strength and hardness of the material by cooling it so that its microstructure transforms to the hardening structure.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Prozess zur Härtung eines zuvor austenitisierten (3.14) Werkstückes, durch Abkühlen (3.45) unter Bedingungen erreicht, die geeignet sind, den Austenit (3.12) nahezu vollständig in Martensit (3.137) und gegebenenfalls Bainit (3.17) umzuwandeln.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlungprozess durch den eine Härte- und Festigkeitssteigerung erreicht wird, in dem das Material mit solcher Geschwindikeit abgekühlt wird, dass ein Härtungsgefüge enstehen kann.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example xml:lang="de">Randschichthärten

Einsatzhärten
Nitrierhärten</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000041 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000041">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000062"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000022"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.143</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">DIN parameter coupling (DIN EN ISO 683-5 Tab.7 ANMERKUNG verbatim): &apos;Die Anlasstemperatur sollte nicht weniger als 50 °C über der Nitriertemperatur liegen.&apos; OWL 2 DL cannot directly express the cross-class arithmetic constraint Anlass-T(Vergüten preceding) &gt;= Nitrier-T(this Nitrieren) + 50 degC; recommended downstream encoding is SHACL (constraint language) or SWRL (rule extension). This rdfs:comment is the pristine v2 deliverable for this constraint.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Nitrieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nitriding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Aufsticken</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A surface hardening process in which nitrogen is supplied to a material&apos;s surface with the goal to increase the nitrogen content in the surface of a sample or part.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Oberflächenhärtungsverfahren bei dem Stickstoff in flüssigem oder gasförmigem Zustand an eine Oberfläche gebracht wird, mit dem Ziel den Stickstoffgehalt in der Oberfläche des Materials zu erhöhen.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Thermochemical treatment (3.207) to produce hard surface layers on workpieces that contain nitrides.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Thermochemische Behandlung (3.207) zur Herstellung der harten Randschichten an Werkstücken, die Nitride enthalten.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit fix (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.143 lemma is &apos;Nitrieren&apos;; DIN 17022-4, DIN 17022-5, and DIN EN ISO 683-5 all use &apos;Nitrieren&apos; exclusively. The hto-edit.owl DE label &apos;Nitridieren&apos; is a non-DIN morphological variant. The canonical &apos;Nitrieren&apos; is hoisted to skos:prefLabel; the legacy &apos;Nitridieren&apos; is demoted to skos:hiddenLabel.</skos:editorialNote>
        <skos:hiddenLabel xml:lang="de">Nitridieren</skos:hiddenLabel>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000042 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000042">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (Durchwärmdauer)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.80 (thnlrd)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>Durchwärmen des Bauteils, sodass Temperaturhomogenität erreicht wird. Anschließend kann ein Halten auf der Zieltemperatur erfolgen.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Durchwärmen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">equalization</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">soaking</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Grundsätzlicher Wärmebehandlungsvorgang, während dessen die Temperaturhomogenisierung im Bauteil erreicht wird.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">essential heat treatment process step during which temperature homogenization is achieved in the component.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote>In practice, the English terms &apos;equalization&apos; and &apos;soaking&apos; are synonymous. The standard DIN EN ISO 4885 is ambiguous about the distinction between &apos;Halten&apos; (§3.185) and &apos;Durchwärmen&apos; (3.80), and also translates &apos;soaking&apos; as &apos;Halten&apos;. The diagram for &apos;§3.80 Durchwärmen&apos; shows the two processes in sequence, whereas the annotation for &apos;Halten&apos; states that the discrete location within an object must be specified. However, I deem this unnecessary, since &apos;Halten&apos;/&apos;holding&apos; refers to the process that follows the soaking step and ensures a homogeneous temperature distribution regardless of the location.

(thnlrd)</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000043 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000043">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Strömungsmaschine</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbo machinery</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A device that extracts energy from or imparts energy to a continuously moving stream of fluid.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000043"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045"/>
        <rdfs:comment>the mechanical energy needed for machines to work is supplied by engines/motors</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Arbeitsmaschine</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">machinery</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A powered machine which takes up mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000043"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Engine supply the mechanical energy to power machinery.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Kraftmaschine</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">engine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel>turbine</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A machine designed to convert one or more forms of energy into mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000046 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000046">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000055"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wind turbine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An engine to convert kinetic energy of a gas (movement of air in the atmosphere, wind) into the rotation of a shaft which drives a generator.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000047 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000047">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000055"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">water turbine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An engine which converts kinetic energy of water into rotational energy of a shaft connected to a generator.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000048 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000048">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000055"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">steam turbine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A machine that extracts thermal energy from pressurized steam and uses it to do mechanical work utilising a rotating output shaft.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000049 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000049">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000056"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbojet engine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>combination of a gas turbine and and a propelling nozzle</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000050 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000050">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compressor</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A machine that increases the pressure of a gas by reducing its volume.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000051 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000051">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">propeller</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A powered machine with a rotating hub and radiating blades which exert linear thrust upon a working fluid such as water or air.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000052 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000052">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbopump</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A machine powered by a gas engine to create high throughput and high pressure flow of fluid media.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000053 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000053">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Ventilator</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fan</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A powered machine that creates airflow.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000054 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000054">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000044"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electric generator</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A machine that converts mechanical energy to electrical energy.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000055 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000055">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbine</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000056 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000056">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat engine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A system that transfers thermal energy to do mechanical or electrical work.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000057 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000057">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000045"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Elektromotor</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electric motor</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">An engine which transforms electric energy into mechanical energy.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000058 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000058">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000056"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">internal combustion engine</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>An engine that uses combustion to turn chemical energy into mechanical energy by the transferral of kinetic energy from pressure increase of hot gas expansion into the movement of engine parts.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example>driven parts can be:
pistons (piston engine)
turbine blades (gas turbine)
rotor (Wankel engine)
nozzle (jet engine).</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000059 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000059">
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000060"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (process-step start instants, operational usage)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">start time</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A temporal instant that specifies the date(time) a process started.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example>09.06.2022 17:48:47</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000060 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000060">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Bild 1 (process-step end instants, operational usage)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">end time</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A temporal instant that specifies the date(time) a process ended.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example>09.06.2022 18:18:47</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000061 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000061">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.185</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="de">Die HoldingTime ist stets mit einer vorhergehende SoakingTime verbunden.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Halten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">holding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Grundsätzlicher Wärmebehandlungsvorgang ohne Temperaturänderung im Ofen.
Teil einer Zeit-Temperatur-Folge, bei dem die Temperatur konstant gehalten wird</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">essential heat treatment process step without temperature change in the furnace after the designated temperature was homogeneously reached within the part.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000062 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000062">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.168</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Abschrecken</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenching</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Grundsätzlicher Wärmebehandlungsvorgang mit stark erhöhter Abkühlgeschwindigkeit, mit dem Ziel der Verhinderung diffusionsgesteuerter Umwandlungen.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Grundsätzlicher Wärmebehandlungsvorgang, bei dem ein Werkstück mit größerer Geschwindigkeit als an ruhender Luft abgekühlt (3.45) wird.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">essential heat treatment process in which a workpiece is cooled (3.45) at a higher rate than in still air.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">essential heat treatment process with significantly increased cooling rate, aimed at preventing diffusion based transformations.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000063 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000063">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">counter</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A data item that describes the position of an entity within a sequential chain of action with an integer value.</skos:definition>
        <skos:example>Numbering of subprocesses in a heat treatment sequence.</skos:example>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000064 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000064">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow rate</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">a process attribute quantifying the volume of a continuous substance that traverses a designated spatial boundary per unit of duration.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000065 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000065">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000064"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (atmosphere flow control)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow rate specification</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Setpoint defining the flow rate of some fluid.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Sollwert einer Durchflussrate für Fluide.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000066 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000066">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000000"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (Plasmanitrieren — Ofendruck &lt; 10 mbar via evacuation, operational)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">evacuation</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">essential heat treatment process that creates a vacuum. Removing atmoshpere and decreasing pressure.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000067 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000067">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">evacuation function</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A heat treatment function to decrease a volume&apos;s pressure to vacuum, removing possibly present gases and fluids.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000068 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000068">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, Tab.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.170</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, Tab.11 Fn e</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Abschreckmittel</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenchant</rdfs:label>
        <skos:editorialNote>needs work</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000069 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000069">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenchant role</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A medium role of a fluid to serve as an intermediary for the transmission of thermal energy from an object to the fluid in a capacity that exeeds the transmission from static air.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000070 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000070">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coolant role</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A medium role of a fluid to serve as an intermediary for the transmission of thermal energy from an object to the fluid.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000071 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000071">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coolant</rdfs:label>
        <skos:editorialNote>needs work</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000072 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000072">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000019"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000116 xml:lang="en">this is really not connected to the phenomenon of case hardening found in mangos</obo:IAO_0000116>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.37 (Einsatzhärten = Aufkohlen + Härten)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Einsatzhärten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">case hardening</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Behandlung bestehend aus Aufkohlen (3.36) oder Carbonitrieren (3.35) mit anschließender Härtung (3.167).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Surface hardening process comprised of carburising, hardening and tempering of case hardnening steels.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Treatment consisting of carburising (3.36) or carbonitriding (3.35) followed by hardening (3.167).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit (2026-06-09, γ refinement): HTO_0000072 (recently added upstream as case-hardening PROCESS) is overlaid here with DE label &apos;Einsatzhärten&apos; and verbatim 4885 §3.37 wording. Earlier draft had a twin class hto:HTO_0000106; removed in favour of this overlay to keep upstream IRIs intact (Q2c style). HTO_0000106 slot vacated for Divya to re-claim. The depth measure CHD is the separate HTO_0000089 — do not conflate process with depth.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000073 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000073">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §9.2 (Bild 7; via DIN 50190-3)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.73</terms:source>
        <terms:source>ISO 18203:2016, §3.4 (acceptance-criterion source — outside DIN corpus)
DIN EN ISO 18203:2022-07 (https://dx.doi.org/10.31030/3344011)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>the defined boundary value usually is set 50 HV above core hardness</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Nitrierhärtetiefe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nitriding hardness depth</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">NHD</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">effective case depth after nitriding</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Distance from the surface of a nitrided or nitrocarburised workpiece to the point at which the hardness equals a defined boundary value.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Senkrechter Abstand von der Oberfläche eines nitrierten oder nitrocarburierten Werkstückes bis zu dem Punkt, an dem die Härte einem Grenzwert entspricht.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit re-IRI (2026-06-09): the legacy class &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/co/HTO_0000039&gt; was misnamespaced under pmd/co/ (should have been pmd/hto/), and the local ID HTO_0000039 collided with &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039&gt; (annealing). Re-IRIed to hto:HTO_0000073 (next free above HTO_0000072 case hardening). owl:equivalentClass preserves A-Box / external compatibility; the legacy IRI is marked owl:deprecated below.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000074 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000074">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §4.2</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.144</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Nitrocarburieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nitrocarburizing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">nitrocarburising</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Thermochemical treatment (3.207) to produce a hard surface layer containing nitrides and nitrocarbides, forming a compound layer and an underlying diffusion layer.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Thermochemische Behandlung (3.207) zur Herstellung einer harten Randschicht, die Nitride und Nitrocarbide enthält, zur Bildung einer Verbindungsschicht und einer darunter liegenden Diffusionsschicht.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit re-IRI (2026-06-09): the legacy class &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/co/HTO_0000063&gt; was misnamespaced under pmd/co/ (should have been pmd/hto/), and the local ID HTO_0000063 collided with &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000063&gt; (counter). Re-IRIed to hto:HTO_0000074. NB: DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.144 Anm.2 records disjointness with Carbonitrieren (HTO_0000075) — the two are NOT synonyms in DIN despite industry colloquial conflation.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000075 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000075">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.35</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Carbonitrieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">carbonitriding</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Thermochemical treatment (3.207) to enrich the surface layer with carbon and nitrogen; carbonitriding is a carburising process (3.36).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Thermochemische Behandlung (3.207), um die Randschicht mit Kohlenstoff und Stickstoff anzureichern; Carbonitrieren ist ein Aufkohlungsprozess (3.36).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit re-IRI (2026-06-09): the legacy class &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/co/HTO_0000064&gt; was misnamespaced under pmd/co/ (should have been pmd/hto/), and the local ID HTO_0000064 collided with &lt;https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000064&gt; (flow rate). Re-IRIed to hto:HTO_0000075. NB: §3.144 Anm.2 disjointness with Nitrocarburieren (HTO_0000074).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000076 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000076">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.33</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.33 Anm.1 (operational vs. thermodynamic contrast)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Kohlenstoffpegel</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">carbon level</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">C-Pegel</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Relational quality describing the carbon content (mass-fraction in %) that an austenitised pure-iron sample assumes in equilibrium with the carburising agent at a specified temperature.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Relationale Eigenschaft, die beschreibt, welchen Kohlenstoffgehalt (als Massenanteil in %), den eine austenitisierte Probe aus Reineisen bei bestimmter Temperatur im Gleichgewicht mit dem Aufkohlungsmittel annimmt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.33 Anm.1 explicitly contrasts &apos;Kohlenstoffpegel&apos; (operationally defined) with &apos;Kohlenstoffpotenzial&apos; (thermodynamic) — the two are NOT synonymous. HTO&apos;s existing Carbon Potential carries the thermodynamic reading; this new class carries the §3.33 operational definition.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000077 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000077">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.12</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Austenit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">austenite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure that is a solid solution of one or more elements in γ-iron (3.91).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Mikrogefüge, das eine feste Lösung eines oder mehrerer Elemente im γ-Eisen (3.91) ist.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote>All term definitions copied from DIN 4885 should be rid of the internal reference number e.g. &quot;3.91&quot; (thnlrd)</skos:editorialNote>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.12 + Tabelle 1. Parent BFO_0000040 (material entity) selected as the closest BFO anchor for a phase as a material-bearer; some HTO maintainers may prefer to re-anchor under a PMDco material-phase class once one is added upstream.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000078 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000078">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.137</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Martensit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">martensite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Gefüge/Phase (3.156), die in kohlenstoffhaltigen Stählen durch Abkühlen (3.45) des Austenits (3.12) gebildet wird, wobei die hohe Geschwindigkeit des Abkühlens verhindert, dass ausreichend Kohlenstoffatome aus der Kristallstruktur diffundieren können, um Zementit (3.39) (Fe3C) zu bilden.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure/phase (3.156) formed in carbon-bearing steels by cooling (3.45) of austenite (3.12), where the high cooling rate prevents sufficient carbon atoms from diffusing out of the crystal structure to form cementite (3.39) (Fe3C).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.137 + Tabelle 1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000079 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000079">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.17</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Bainit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bainite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure resulting from a transformation of austenite (3.12) at temperatures above the martensite (3.137) start temperature (Ms) and outside the range of pearlite (3.155), consisting of ferrite laths with carbides arranged either within (lower bainite) or between (upper bainite) the ferrite laths.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Mikrogefüge, das aus einer Umwandlung von Austenit (3.12) resultiert bei Temperaturen über die Starttemperatur (Ms) von Martensit (3.137) und außerhalb des Bereichs von Perlit (3.155), der aus Ferritlatten und Carbiden besteht, die entweder innerhalb der Ferritlatten (untere Bainite) oder zwischen den Ferritlatten angeordnet sind (obere Bainite).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.17 + Tabelle 1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000080 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000080">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.85</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Ferrit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ferrite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Gefüge von Eisen oder Stahl mit kubisch-raumzentrierter Gitterstruktur.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure of iron or steel with a body-centred cubic lattice structure.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.85 + Tabelle 1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000081 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000081">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.155</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Perlit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pearlite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Aus Ferrit- (3.85) und Zementit- (3.39) Lamellen bestehender Gefügebestandteil, der durch die eutektoidische Austenitumwandlung (3.56) und der gleichzeitig ablaufenden Transformation in Ferrit und Zementit gebildet wird.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure constituent consisting of ferrite (3.85) and cementite (3.39) lamellae, formed by the eutectoidic transformation of austenite (3.56) and the concomitant transformation into ferrite and cementite.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.155 + Tabelle 1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000082 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000082">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, Tabelle 1 (Fe-C-Phasen)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.39</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Zementit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cementite</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Microstructure composed of iron carbide with composition Fe3C.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Mokrogefüge, das das Carbid des Eisens, mit der Zusammensetzung Fe3C ist.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Fe-C phase from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.39 + Tabelle 1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000083 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000083">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Martensit-Starttemperatur</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">martensite start temperature</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">M_s</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Ms</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Temperatur, bei der die Umwandlung von Austenit in Martensit (3.137) beim Abkühlen (3.45) beginnt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Temperature at which the transformation of austenite into martensite (3.137) begins upon cooling (3.45).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1 (Bei Stählen können im Wesentlichen folgende Umwandlungstemperaturen unterschieden werden).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000084 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000084">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Martensit-Endtemperatur</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">martensite finish temperature</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">M_f</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Mf</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Temperatur, bei der die Umwandlung von Austenit in Martensit beim Abkühlen annähernd vollständig ist.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Temperature at which the transformation of austenite into martensite is approximately complete upon cooling.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000085 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000085">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">A1 transformation temperature</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">A1-Temperatur</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">A1</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">A_1</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Equilibrium temperature defining the lower limit of austenite (3.12) existence.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Gleichgewichts-Temperatur, die die untere Grenze der Existenz von Austenit (3.12) festlegt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000086 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000086">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">A3 transformation temperature</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">A3-Temperatur</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">A3</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">A_3</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Equilibrium temperature defining the upper limit of ferrite (3.85) existence.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Gleichgewichts-Temperatur, die die obere Grenze der Existenz von Ferrit (3.85) festlegt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000087 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000087">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Am transformation temperature</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Am-Temperatur</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">A_m</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Acm</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Am</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Equilibrium temperature defining the upper limit of cementite (3.39) existence in a hypereutectoid steel (3.117).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Gleichgewichts-Temperatur, die die obere Grenze der Existenz von Zementit (3.39) in einem übereutektoidischen Stahl (3.117) festlegt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1. 4885 names this &apos;Am&apos;; the &apos;Acm&apos; altLabel is the IIW/ASM-standard naming retained for industry compatibility.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000088 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000088">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.74</terms:source>
        <terms:source>ISO 18203:2016, §3.5 (modifiziert)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Einhärtungstiefe nach Randschichthärten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">surface hardening depth</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Randschichthärtungstiefe</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Rht</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">SHD</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Abstand von der Oberfläche bis zu dem Punkt, an dem die Vickers-Härte (HV) 80 % des für die Oberflächenhärte geforderten Mindestwertes für das entsprechende Werkstück beträgt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Distance from the surface to the point at which the Vickers hardness (HV) equals 80% of the minimum required surface hardness for the workpiece.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): surface hardening depth (Rht) from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.74 (sourced from ISO 18203:2016 §3.5 modified). Distinct from CHD (HTO_0000089) which is the depth measure for Einsatzhärten.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000089 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000089">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.72</terms:source>
        <terms:source>ISO 18203:2016, §3.1 (modifiziert)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Einsatzhärtungstiefe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">case hardening depth</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">CHD</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Einsatzhärtungs-Härtetiefe</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Abstand von der Oberfläche eines Werkstückes bis zu einem die Dicke der gehärteten (3.167) Schicht festlegenden Punkt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Distance from the surface of a workpiece to a point defining the thickness of the hardened (3.167) case.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): case hardening depth (CHD) from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.72 (sourced from ISO 18203:2016 §3.1 modified). IMPORTANT: CHD is the depth MEASURE; do NOT confuse with hto:HTO_0000072 &apos;case hardening&apos; which is the PROCESS (Einsatzhärten).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000090 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000090">
        <obo:IAO_0100001 rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000088"/>
        <rdfs:comment>unnecessary grouping term</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">OBSOLETE Oberflächenhärtungstiefe</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">OBSOLETE surface hardening depth (generic)</rdfs:label>
        <owl:deprecated rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</owl:deprecated>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">OBSOLETE Generic depth term for surface hardening; in industrial practice referred to as Surface Hardening Depth (SHD); in DIN normation usually narrowed to Rht (§3.74) or CHD (§3.72).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">OBSOLETE Generischer Tiefenbegriff für Randschichthärtungen, in der industriellen Praxis als &apos;Surface Hardening Depth&apos; (SHD) verwendet; nach DIN-Normierung in der Regel präzisiert zu Rht (§3.74) oder CHD (§3.72).</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000091 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000091">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.103</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Härtbarkeit</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hardenability</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Relational quality describing the ability of steels to transform into martensite (3.137) and/or bainite (3.17).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Relationale Eigschenschaft, die die Fähigkeit von Stählen beschreibt, zu Martensit (3.137) und/oder Bainit (3.17) umzuwandeln.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): material quality from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.103. The §3.103 Anm.1 notes that Härtbarkeit is frequently quantified via the Stirnabschreckversuch (HTO_0000092).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000092 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000092">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0009006"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000091"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.128</terms:source>
        <terms:source>ISO 642 (Jominy end-quench test procedure)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Jominy end-quench test</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Stirnabschreckversuch</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Jominy test</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Jominy-Versuch</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Assay that is a standardised test method for assessing hardenability (3.103).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Ein Assay bzw. genormtes Prüfverfahren zur Beurteilung der Härtbarkeit (3.103).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): test method from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.128. Reinforcing standards: ISO 642 (test procedure).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000093 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000093">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.186</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-2:2018, §7.2 (+A delivery state)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Weichglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">soft annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) to reduce the hardness of a ferrous product to a specified level.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108) zum Vermindern der Härte eines Eisenerzeugnisses auf eine vorgegebene Stufe.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.186. Aligns with DIN EN ISO 683-2 +A delivery state (weichgeglüht).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000094 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000094">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.146</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-7:2025, §6.2.1 (+N delivery state)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Normalglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">normalizing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) aimed at refining and homogenising the grain size (3.99) of a ferrous product, consisting of heating (3.109) to a temperature slightly above A3 (A1 for hypereutectoid steels (3.117)), without prolonged soaking, followed by suitable cooling (3.45) to achieve a fine ferrite-pearlite microstructure.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108) mit dem Ziel, die Korngröße (3.99) eines Eisenerzeugnisses zu verfeinern und schließlich einheitlicher zu machen, bestehend aus Erwärmen (3.109) auf eine Temperatur wenig oberhalb A3 (A1 bei übereutektoidischen Stählen (3.117)), ohne längeres Halten bei dieser Temperatur, und anschließendem zweckmäßigen Abkühlen (3.45) bis zum Erreichen eines feinen ferritisch-perlitischen Gefüges.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.146. Aligns with DIN EN ISO 683-7 +N delivery state.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000095 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000095">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.197</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-7:2025, §6.2.1 (+SR delivery state)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Spannungsarmglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stress-relief annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Spannungsarmgluehen</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">stress relieving</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Annealing (3.8) at temperatures below A1 to reduce internal stresses without substantially altering the microstructure of a workpiece or ferrous product, followed by slow cooling (3.45).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Glühen (3.8) bei Temperaturen unterhalb A1 zur Reduzierung der inneren Spannungen ohne das Gefüge eines Werkstückes oder Eisenerzeugnisses substantiell zu verändern, bis zu einer Stufe auf der die inneren Spannungen verringert werden, mit anschließendem langsamen Abkühlen (3.45).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.197. Aligns with DIN EN ISO 683-7 +SR delivery state.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000096 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000096">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.64</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Diffusionsglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diffusion annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">homogenization annealing</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) / annealing (3.8) of ferrous products or workpieces to reduce segregation (3.179) and promote homogeneity through diffusion (3.63).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108)/Glühen (3.8) von Eisenerzeugnissen oder Werkstücken, um die Seigerung (3.179) zu verringern und die Homogenität durch Diffusion (3.63) zu fördern.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.64.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000097 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000097">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.29</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Blankglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bright annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Annealing (3.8) in a medium under conditions that prevent oxidation (3.150) and preserve the original surface quality.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Glühen (3.8) in einem Mittel unter solchen Bedingungen, dass eine Oxidation (3.150) verhindert wird und die ursprüngliche Oberflächenqualität beibehalten wird.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.29.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000098 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000098">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.174</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Rekristallisationsglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">recrystallization annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">recrystallisation annealing</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Annealing (3.8) to eliminate the strength increase from cold deformation and to renew grains via nucleation without phase change (3.156).</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Glühen (3.8) zur Beseitigung der Festigkeitszunahme nach Kaltumformung und Kornneubildung durch Keimbildung ohne Änderung der Phase (3.156).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.174.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000099 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000099">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.122</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">inter-critical annealing</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">zwischenkritisches Glühen</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">zwischenkritische Behandlung</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Annealing (3.8) of a hypoeutectoid steel (3.118), consisting of heating (3.109) and soaking at temperatures between A1 and A3 to partially produce austenit, followed by suitable cooling (3.45) tailored to the required properties.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Glühen (3.8) eines untereutektoidischen Stahls (3.118), bestehend aus Erwärmen (3.109) und Halten auf Temperaturen zwischen A1 und A3, um teilweise Austenit zu erzeugen, und anschließendem zweckentsprechenden Abkühlen (3.45), angepasst an die geforderten Eigenschaften.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.122.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000100 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000100">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.127</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.8 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">isothermal transformation</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">isothermes Umwandeln</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">isothermal annealing</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) with austenitising (3.14), interrupted cooling (3.45), and isothermal hold at a specified temperature until transformation is complete.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108) mit Austenitisieren (3.14) und unterbrochenem Abkühlen (3.45) und Konstanthaltung auf eine bestimmte Temperatur bis zur vollständigen Umwandlung.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.127. NB: 4885 §3.8 Anm.1 lists &apos;isothermes Umwandeln&apos; as one of the named Glühen children.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000101 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000101">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.188</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Lösungsglühen</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solution annealing</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">Lösungsbehandeln</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">solution treating</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) consisting of austenitising (3.14) at a high temperature followed by sufficiently rapid cooling (3.45) to prevent new precipitation upon return to ambient temperature.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108), bestehend aus Austenitisieren (3.14) auf eine hohe Temperatur mit anschließendem ausreichendem schnellen Abkühlen (3.45), um neue Ausscheidungen nach der Rückkehr zur Umgebungstemperatur zu verhindern.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.188.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000102 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000102">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000039"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.8 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.89</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">full annealing</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">vollständiges Glühen</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="de">kritisches Glühen</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Annealing (3.8) to achieve a spheroidal microstructure (see 3.190), which involves complete austenitisation (3.14) to a temperature above A3 (for hypoeutectoid steels) or above A1 (for hypereutectoid steels), followed by slow cooling (3.45), to achieve a microstructure close to thermodynamic equilibrium.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Glühen (3.8) zur Erzielung von kugeligem Gefüge (siehe 3.190), was ein vollständiges Austenitisieren (3.14) auf eine Temperatur oberhalb von A3 (bei hypoeutektoiden Stählen) bzw. oberhalb von A1 (bei hypereutektoiden Stählen) beinhaltet, gefolgt von einer langsamen Abkühlung (3.45), um eine Mikrostruktur zu erzielen, die dem thermodynamischen Gleichgewicht nahekommt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): Glühen-family subclass from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.89 (Full annealing — listed inline in §3.8 Anm.1 as a named Glühen child). Definition is paraphrased per 4885 conventions; the §3.89 verbatim entry uses generic &apos;Wärmebehandlung&apos;.</skos:editorialNote>
        <skos:editorialNote>deviating from the standard here because &apos;full annealing&apos; ist supposed to fully transform the microstructure into austenite (hence the name) whereas comparable annealing procedures do not fully transform the material even though they are within the same T-range (normalizing, intercritical annealing). Additional info and explanation provided by TWaldenmaier. (thnlrd)</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000103 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000103">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.11</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Austempern</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">austempering</rdfs:label>
        <skos:comment xml:lang="en">In practical use, the terms bainitising and austempering are used interchangeably cheifly in US-american english. (thnlrd)</skos:comment>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Isothermal heat treatment to produce a bainitic (cf. 3.17, 3.18) or ausferritic (cf. 3.9) microstructure in a workpiece.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Isotherme Wärmebehandlung zur Herstellung eines bainitischen (siehe 3.17 und 3.18) oder ausferritischen (siehe 3.9) Gefüges eines Werkstückes.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): isothermal-treatment process from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.11. Closely related to Bainitisieren (HTO_0000104, §3.18).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000104 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000104">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.18</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Bainitisieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bainitising</rdfs:label>
        <skos:comment xml:lang="en">In practical use, the terms bainitising and austempering are used interchangeably cheifly in US-american english. (thnlrd)</skos:comment>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Austenitisieren (3.14) und Abschrecken (3.168) auf eine Temperatur oberhalb Ms und isothermes Halten auf dieser Temperatur, um sicherzustellen, dass sich der Austenit (3.12) in Bainit (3.17) umwandelt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Austenitising (3.14) and quenching (3.168) to a temperature above Ms followed by isothermal hold at that temperature so that austenite (3.12) transforms into bainite (3.17).</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): process from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.18.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000105 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000105">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.154</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Patentieren</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">patenting</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Heat treatment (3.108) consisting of austenitising (3.14) followed by suitable cooling (3.45) to produce a microstructure favourable for subsequent drawing or roll-drawing of wire or strip.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Wärmebehandlung (3.108), bestehend aus Austenitisieren (3.14) und anschließendem geeigneten Abkühlen (3.45), um ein für das nachfolgende Ziehen oder Ziehwalzen von Draht oder Band günstiges Gefüge zu erreichen.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): process from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.154.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000106 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000106">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hardened material</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000107 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000107">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000040"/>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.184</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Einfachhärten</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">single hardening</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">In einem Schritt durchgeführtes Härten nach vorausgegangenem Aufkohlen (3.36) und langsamem Abkühlen (3.45) auf Raumtemperatur.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Single-step hardening following prior carburising (3.36) and slow cooling (3.45) to room temperature.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): hardening sub-process from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.184 (siehe Bild 1 b).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000108 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000108">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.213 Anm.1</terms:source>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Mx transformation temperature</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Mx-Temperatur</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">M_x</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Mx</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Temperatur, bei der beim Abkühlen x % Volumenanteil Austenit in Martensit umgewandelt wurden.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Temperature at which, upon cooling, x % volume fraction of austenite has transformed into martensite.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit addition (2026-06-09): transition temperature from DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.213 Anm.1 (parametric x ∈ (0,100)).</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000109 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000109">
        <obo:IAO_0000114>needs work</obo:IAO_0000114>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §7 (generic multi-chamber furnace construction)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment>moved to fiat object part. correct if every furnace has a chamber</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="de">unklare Zuordnung innerhalb der SDCs. Eine Kammer existiert nur als Teil eines Gerätes (Device), könnte aber selbst noch einmal als independent continuant definiert werden, da sich in der Kammer Chargen, Gestelle, Thermoelemente etc. befinden.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chamber</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Systemboundary of a distinct Heattreatment Process. Includes a fluid that has the role of medium role (e.g., Helium or Vacuum).</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000110 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000110">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000109"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §7 (Ofen-Konstruktion)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §10</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Heizkammer</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heating chamber</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Distinguishable chamber of a heat treatment furnace with a heater.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Ofenkammer mit einer Heizung</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000111 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000111">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000109"/>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §7.2 (Abschreckeinrichtung)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §10.3 (Fassungsverhältnis ≥ 6× Chargengewicht)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Abschreckkammer</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">quenching chamber</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Chamber of a heat treatment furnace that is designed to quench objects.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Kammer eines Wärmebehandlungsofens, die zum Abschrecken von Gegenständen bestimmt ist.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000112 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000112">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.33 (Kohlenstoffpegel — contrast Anm.1)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 (carburising atmosphere control)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="de">Nitrocarburieren mit Kohlenstoffträger, aus Messwerten abgeleitet KC</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">See standard DIN 1310</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Kohlenstoffpotential</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">carbon potential</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Carbon content of a specimen of pure iron in equilibrium with a carbourizing medium under specific conditions.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 §3.33 names the operational quantity &apos;Kohlenstoffpegel&apos; (carbon level), with §3.33 Anm.1 contrasting it explicitly with the &apos;thermodynamisches Kohlenstoffpotenzial&apos;. 4885 treats the two as NOT synonymous. hto:CarbonPotential is retained as the thermodynamic-potential quality; the new sibling hto:HTO_0000076 (CarbonLevel) carries the §3.33 operational definition. See hto:HTO_0000076 below for the sibling class.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000113 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000113">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 eq.3 (K_N = p_{NH3} / p_{H2}^{1.5})</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">The nitriding potential is a key indicator how intensive the nitriding process is, the higher the value the stronger the nitriding conditions, unit is bar^-3/2</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Nitrierkennzahl</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nitrogen potential</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A relational quality describing the intensity of a nitriding atmosphere by relating the partial pressures of ammonia and hydrogen gas.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000114 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000114">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 eq.3 (p_NH3, p_H2 in K_N formula)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">Partialdruck</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">partial pressure</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">Realtional quality describing the contribution from a single gas species to the total pressure in a gas mixture.</skos:definition>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="de">Relationale Eigenschaft die den Beitrag eines Gases zum Gesamtdruck in einem Gasgemisch beschreibt.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit (2026-06-09): DIN EN ISO 4885 has no §3 entry for partial pressure; this is upstream physical-chemistry vocabulary, not DIN-terminology-native. Operational usage in DIN 17022-4 §7.3 (p_NH3, p_H2 in K_N formula) is the only DIN anchor.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000116 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000116">
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000080"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000109"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-1:1994, §7 (chamber/Ofen-Konstruktion)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (Ofendruck)</terms:source>
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 4885:2018, §3.165 (Ofenatmosphäre, related quality)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Effective atmosphere pressure in chamber to keep process save must be 2-3 mbar above ambient pressure.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chamber pressure</rdfs:label>
        <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">atmosphere pressure</skos:altLabel>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A pressure which inheres within the confines (atmosphere) of an oven chamber.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000117 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000117">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000032"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000136"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000043"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>seam to be a device specification pinting to a process charateristic of type speed</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotation speed specification</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A setpoint describing the intended rotational speed of a device e.g. an fan or turbine.</skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote>needs work</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000118 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000118">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (Taupunkt as carburising atmosphere control variable)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dew point</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">dew point of the atmosphere, measured during process or calculated from lambda / oxygen probe signal </skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000118"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.org/dc/terms/source"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (Taupunkt as carburising atmosphere control variable)</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <skos:editorialNote>the source given (DIN EN ISO 683-3) does not contain info about dew points (thoni)</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000119 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000119">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-4:1998, §7.3 (H2 atmosphere monitoring, p_H2 in K_N formula)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">nominal pre-set value of control system for hydrogen probe </rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydrogene sensor signal</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">measured hydrogen value of  hydrogen probe measured in milli volt </skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000120 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000120">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (atmosphere-control umbrella; lambda probe is industry-vendor term for the O2 probe class)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">lambda probe signal</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">measured lambda probe signal in exhaust gas </skos:definition>
        <skos:editorialNote xml:lang="en">DIN audit (2026-06-09): &apos;Lambdasonde&apos; is not explicitly named in DIN 683-3 §A.4 (it uses the generic &apos;Sauerstoffsonde&apos;); the lambda probe is a specific O2-probe variant used for burner stoichiometry in fuel-fired furnaces. Provenance is operational / inferred, not direct.</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000120"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.org/dc/terms/source"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (atmosphere-control umbrella; lambda probe is industry-vendor term for the O2 probe class)</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <skos:editorialNote>the source given (DIN EN ISO 683-3) does not contain info about lambda probes or oxygen (thnlrd)</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000121 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000121">
        <terms:source>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (Sauerstoffsonde / O2 probe for Cp atmosphere control)</terms:source>
        <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">oxygen probe signal</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">A measurement datum generated by an electrochemical or optical sensor, representing the specific concentration of elemental oxygen within a sampled medium.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    <owl:Axiom>
        <owl:annotatedSource rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000121"/>
        <owl:annotatedProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.org/dc/terms/source"/>
        <owl:annotatedTarget>DIN EN ISO 683-3:2022, §A.4 Anm. (Sauerstoffsonde / O2 probe for Cp atmosphere control)</owl:annotatedTarget>
        <skos:editorialNote>the source given (DIN EN ISO 683-3) does not contain info about oxygen probes (thnlrd)</skos:editorialNote>
    </owl:Axiom>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000122 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/hto/HTO_0000122">
        <terms:source>DIN 17022-3:2025-11, §6</terms:source>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="de">Potentiell ableitbar mit bestimmten Fluss-Schwellenwerten</rdfs:comment>
